On 12/13/2024 at 07:39 PM, Christine Moyer wrote:
To:Robert Moyer (First Viewed: 12/13/2024 at 07:41 PM)
Subject:Re: Adrian
He should be fine for tomorrow at 9:15 pick up
On 12/13/2024 at 05:52 PM, Robert Moyer wrote:
To:Christine Moyer (First Viewed: 12/13/2024 at 07:38 PM)
Subject:Re: Adrian
I’m getting worried because I don’t know how you plan to communicate or plan going into a Friday night again. Kari and Alan, and of course
AD and me don’t know if plans are changing tomorrow or not.
That puts me in an uncomfortable position to try and nudge you given past history and four people could be impacted. I don’t like being the
“nudger.” That is why I asked for two minutes on the phone.
This makes me feel uncomfortable.
On 12/13/2024 at 03:11 PM, Robert Moyer wrote:
To:Christine Moyer (First Viewed: 12/13/2024 at 07:40 PM)
Subject:Re: Adrian
I don’t know? Doesn’t he have Kari? Can we just talk for three minutes and I can let Alan know?
On 12/13/2024 at 03:06 PM, Christine Moyer wrote:
To:Robert Moyer (First Viewed: 12/13/2024 at 03:10 PM)
Subject:Re: Adrian
What start time? We have an engagement that I asked he be home by 5:30 tomorrow.,
On 12/13/2024 at 02:59 PM, Robert Moyer wrote:
To:Christine Moyer (First Viewed: 12/13/2024 at 03:06 PM)
Subject:Re: Adrian
Sent an email reply to Kari's mail just to you.
<Rob Moyer to Christine>
Can we sync on AD plans given he feels crummy?
I would rather him start a bit later in the day and still make it than force an early start to make this time here. And go straight into a session. Just
hearing that already sounds draining to me.
But if we shift it might work better and we can all couch camp. It’s and idea because I don’t want a big backlog of makeups which could
otherwise be Thurs, tomorrow, maybe Whistler Sat... ?
